  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(ActionAid) Citizens for Accountability in Public Service Financing (CAPSF)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will focus on the education sector at the village and township-levels where local education is an underfunded area of high priority for communities. It will mobilise citizens, civil society, the media, and government and elected officials to engage in concrete ways in the development of national and state/regional and township budgets. 

Objective 1: To build the capacity of targeted groups to participate in, and to analyse the response of, public service financing at different levels: national, state/regional and local level

Objective 2: To strengthen national media to create the space for, and promote citizens&#xBF; participation in, budgetary processes, and to influence parliamentarians and government officials to be responsive to people&#xBF;s priorities in public financing</narrative>
  </description>
